cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.MA, cs.CE, cs.NI 

This paper deals with the spreading of epidemics and awareness on multiplex networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper focuses on the diffusion of information and disease on networks. The second likely category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), as the paper investigates the interplay between social behavior and disease spread. The third likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), as the paper uses a microscopic Markov chain approach to model the dynamics of the spreading processes. The fourth likely category is cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), as the paper discusses the impact of awareness diffusion on the immunization of the physical contact network. The fifth likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with the dynamics of spreading processes on multiplex networks.
